-- Euro, bond yields rise as Draghi gives no hint QE imminent 
-- By London markets team
-- Thu Oct 02, 2014 09:12AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Oct 2 (Reuters) - The euro gained against the dollar while euro zone bond yields rose on Thursday as European Central Bank President Mario Draghi gave no hints of an imminent sovereign bond buying programme in his post-meeting news conference.

For Draghi's comments click on [ID:nECBNEWS] "The market is at highs and in order for us to sustain these levels we need to have more indications of quantitative easing, which Draghi is not giving us," a bond trader said. German Bund futures <FGBLc1> fell as low as 149.92, down 29 ticks on the day, compared with 150.10 before the speech. Euro zone bond yields rose 2-4 basis points. The FTSEurofirst 300 index <.FTEU3> of top European shares extended losses and was down 1 percent at 1,354.60 points.